    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-10T00:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-10T00:36:00-05:00" n="951"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d951">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/13735.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Canova</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Aguascalientes</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-09T23:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 9, 1914, 11 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The committee sent by the Convention to see Carranza telegraph Gutiérrez that
                    Carranza now asks for more time and states his willingness to deliver the
                    Executive Power if the Convention will elect the Provisional President not for
                    twenty days but until the constitutional president is elected and inaugurated.
                    This would take two weeks and upset the work of the Convention, therefore
                    inadmissible.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Canova</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
